6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to crimes and punishments; amending
21 O.S. 2021, Section 701.9, which relates to
8 penalties for murder; establishing penalty for
certain persons convicted of murder in the first
9 degree; and providing an effective date.
10
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 21 O.S. 2021, Section 701.9, is
14 amended to read as follows:
15 Section 701.9. A. 1. A person who is convicted of or pleads
16 guilty or nolo contendere to murder in the first degree shall be
17 punished by death, by imprisonment for life without parole or by
18 imprisonment for life. A person who is convicted of or pleads
19 guilty or nolo contendere to murder in the first degree, as
20 described in subsection E of Section 701.7 of this title, shall be
21 punished by death or by life without parole and absent an
22 overwhelming amount of mitigating evidence shall not be entitled to
23 or afforded the benefit of receiving imprisonment for life or
24 deferment of the sentence.
Req. No. 10079 Page 1

1 2. A foreign-born person who, at the time of committing murder
2 in the first degree, was present in the United States without valid
3 immigration documentation or violated the terms of his or her
4 admission to the United States, is convicted of or pleads guilty or
5 nolo contendere to murder in the first degree shall be punished by
6 death.
7 B. A person who is convicted of or pleads guilty or nolo
8 contendere to murder in the second degree shall be guilty of a
9 felony punishable by imprisonment in the custody of the Department
10 of Corrections for not less than ten (10) years nor more than life.
11 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
